<paragraph id="D72B4D7279EF8B8D35EBAD31DD4B696B" pageId="0" pageNumber="51">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2AD319C58D639DDD3B3F39BC8D000484" pageId="0" pageNumber="51">
<bibRefCitation id="DA9349362E6117E08F127D8510FB8DEF" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4644.1.1" author="Takemoto, T" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" pagination="001 - 062" refId="B29" refString="Takemoto, T, 2019. Revision of the genus Zeugophora (Coleoptera, Megalopodidae, Zeugophorinae) in Japan. Zootaxa 4644 (1): 001 - 062, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4644.1.1" title="Revision of the genus Zeugophora (Coleoptera, Megalopodidae, Zeugophorinae) in Japan." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.4644.1.1" volume="4644" year="2019">Takemoto (2019)</bibRefCitation>
restored 
<taxonomicName id="716B8BDE880F12B0897506D5CE114E8F" authorityName="Li &amp; Liang" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Jacoby" baseAuthorityYear="1885" class="Insecta" family="Megalopodidae" genus="Zeugophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zeugophora (Pedrillia) nigricollis" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigricollis" subGenus="Pedrillia">Zeugophora (Pedrillia) nigricollis</taxonomicName>
Jacoby, 1885 to a valid species from the synonymy of Z. (
<taxonomicName id="CA6214E7CA3803DCBDA0295CE9E5D855" genus="P." lsidName="P." pageId="0" pageNumber="51" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="522CF2053D2682E3C900573FC45E23ED" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="51">P.</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<taxonomicName id="7B864C217CB91A5850820370D24FA14A" genus="P." lsidName="bicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" rank="species" species="bicolor">
<emphasis id="F3688D9AD9B7EC5D0CB3A8C6B444B2D8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="51">bicolor</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Kraatz, 1879). This species is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="AA375C7CF7F01A52C9E72C7FD0FFD5DC" authorityName="Kraatz" authorityYear="1879" class="Insecta" family="Megalopodidae" genus="Zeugophora" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Zeugophora (Pedrillia) bicolor" order="Coleoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicolor" subGenus="Pedrillia">Zeugophora (Pedrillia) bicolor</taxonomicName>
Kraatz, 1879 in having the black and brown color, but differs in having the pronotum entirely black, the median lobe less curved in the lateral view, the median lobe slender, with the apex of the median lobe triangular and blunt (the base of the pronotum is slightly brown, median lobe is more curved in the lateral view, median lobe slightly broader, and apex of median lobe narrower and sharper in 
<taxonomicName id="3F19DBF20777418B684E2AA48F4C769F" genus="Z." lsidName="Z. (P.) bicolor" pageId="0" pageNumber="51" rank="species" species="bicolor" subGenus="P.">Z. (P.) bicolor</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
